  "source_file": "data\\raw\\detectiveqa\\novel_data_en\\79-有翼之暗-麻耶雄嵩.txt",
  "chunk_index": 36,
  "summary": "Jian Yan and MacArthur observe a small boat in the middle of a lake that appears to be filled with corpses. MacArthur reveals that he had previously checked the boat but left the scene intact to preserve evidence for the police. After instructing Mr. Sugiyama to contact the police chief, Jian Yan and MacArthur board a different boat to investigate. MacArthur explains that he had untied the original boat to let it drift, a move intended to prevent the killer from changing their mind.\n\nAs they approach the second boat, Jian Yan discovers two identical naked female corpses wearing scarlet spring robes. The twins, Kanae and Miyuki, have been beheaded, and blood has stained the peony patterns on their clothing. MacArthur insists they return to shore immediately to avoid disturbing the scene.\n\nHours later, Detective Kubo and forensic investigators arrive. The detective determines the murders occurred between 1:30 and 2:30 pm and concludes the twins were beheaded in the boat. The housekeeper, Auntie Daya, and other witnesses, including Kaname and Yayoi, are unable to distinguish between the two sisters due to their identical appearances. Hirukawa discovers a note in one of the victims' sleeves containing a crude sketch of a lake, an arrow pointing to a dock, the time \"2:00,\" and the word \"secret.\" The clumsy, left-handed handwriting suggests the killer used the note to lure the twins to the lakeside. Amidst the investigation, Jian Yan encounters Yuki-draw and later discusses the cruelty of the event with Mifumi.",
